  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was some people that deliver some mail, some letter personally.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was obviously some kind of ultimatum, not a friendly letter that's what we were supposed to do.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It already is not desirable Jewish people to live in this area.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were kind of-- all the conversations, of course, everything start to, to have completely different tones, completely different character.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I felt-- of course, I was quite young in the time, that they were speaking about one or other Jew being beaten or been done something in his store or his business, and that they suspected some changes to happen without saying exactly what.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this-- what happened, actually, was something that was expected, obviously, to happen that we have to move our-- out of our home.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I-- much later on, I understood actually what really what happening and, and how the, the society, the community of the capital, actually was moving and how, little by little, the government was absorb of the fascist elements that took totally the, the power, political power, in their hands.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The minister became, if I recall the name, Bogdan Filov, one very power, very strong anti-Semite.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Actually, I should say that basically, the attitude of the, the Bulgarian people were pretty sympathetic toward the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] those people that were in power, they wanted very much to please to their much more stronger, more powerful allies, which were the German.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Bulgaria was basically Germanophile country, country that were quite strongly attached with Germany from a much earlier period of time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Matter of fact, the king of Bulgaria was descending from the German Coburg dynasty there.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
